.TH git-init "Mar 2026" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git init \- Initialize git in the current repository.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgit init\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
After initializing git, run the following steps to setup a new remote:
.IP \(bu
Make an initial commit.
.IP \(bu
Ensure the branch name is main.
.br
git branch -M main
.IP \(bu
Add a remote.
.br
git remote add origin <url | ssh>
.IP \(bu
Push the main branch to the remote and configure the upstream.
.br
git push -u origin main
